From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

English

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From inspect +‎ -er.

Noun

[edit]

inspecter (plural inspecters)

  1. Archaic form of inspector.

Synonyms

[edit]
  • inspector

Anagrams

[edit]
  • 'prentices, in respect, prentices, prescient, reinspect

French

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ɛ̃s.pɛk.te/
  • Audio:(file)
  • Audio (France (Somain)):(file)

Verb

[edit]

inspecter

  1. to inspect
